    <preface id="preface" lang="en">
        <title>Preface</title>
        <para>This Manual provides the required information for CUBA-based
            <firstterm>business applications</firstterm>
            development. Business applications are understood here as a wide range of information systems intended for
            enterprise operations support, management and decision-making.
        </para>
        <section id="audience">
            <title>Intended Audience</title>
            <para>This Manual is intended for developers who design business applications using
                <application>CUBA</application>
                platform. The effective use of the platform requires knowledge of the following technologies:
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Java Standard Edition</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Relational databases (SQL, DDL)</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>To get a deeper understanding of the underlying principles of the platform, it is useful to be
                familiar with the following technologies and frameworks:
            </para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Gradle build system</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Spring Framework</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Java Persistence API</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Vaadin web applications framework</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>HTML / CSS / JavaScript</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Java Servlets</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Java Swing</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
        <section id="additional_info">
            <title>Further Reading</title>
            <para>This Manual and the accompanying documentation related to CUBA platform can be found at<ulink
                    url="https://www.cuba-platform.com/en/manual">https://www.cuba-platform.com/en/manual</ulink>.
            </para>
            <para>Below is the list of extra sources on<application>Spring Framework</application>,<application>
                OpenJPA</application>,
                <application>Vaadin</application>
                and<application>Gradle</application>:
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <ulink url="http://projects.spring.io/spring-framework">
                                http://projects.spring.io/spring-framework
                            </ulink>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <ulink url="http://openjpa.apache.org/builds/2.2.2/apache-openjpa/docs/main.html">
                                http://openjpa.apache.org/builds/2.2.2/apache-openjpa/docs/main.html
                            </ulink>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <ulink url="https://vaadin.com/book">https://vaadin.com/book</ulink>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <ulink url="http://www.gradle.org/docs/1.12/userguide/userguide.html">
                                http://www.gradle.org/docs/1.12/userguide/userguide.html
                            </ulink>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
        </section>
